    i5.las2peer.api.Service.logError(Exception)
    Use L2pLogger instead!

    Writes an exception log message Additionally the stack trace is printed.
    i5.las2peer.api.Service.logError(int, Agent, String)
    Use i5.las2peer.logging.L2pLogger#logEvent(Event, Agent, String) instead!

    Writes an error message. The given index (1-99) can be used to differentiate between different log messages.
    i5.las2peer.security.Context.logError(Object, int, String, Agent, Agent)
    Use L2pLogger#logEvent(Object, Event, String, Agent, Agent) instead!

    Writes an error message. The given index (1-99) can be used to differentiate between different log messages. The serviceAgent and userAgent can be set to null if not known. Then this message will not be monitored by the monitoring observer.
    i5.las2peer.security.Context.logError(Object, String)
    Use L2pLogger#logEvent(Object, Event, String) with NodeObserver.Event.SERVICE_ERROR instead!

    Logs an error message to the l2p system using the observers. Since this method will/should only be used in an L2pThread, the message will come from a service or a helper, so a SERVICE_MESSAGE is assumed. Then this message will not be monitored by the monitoring observer.
    i5.las2peer.api.Service.logError(String)
    Use i5.las2peer.logging.L2pLogger#logEvent(Event, String) with NodeObserver.Event.SERVICE_ERROR instead!

    Writes an error log message.
